1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on using radiomics and deep learning techniques for skin cancer detection, which falls under the domain of computer vision.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses deep multi-column radiomic sequencers for high-throughput discovery and extraction of custom radiomic features, which involves machine learning techniques.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning techniques for skin cancer detection, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the extraction of radiomic features from medical imaging data, which can be considered as a form of information retrieval.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with medical imaging data, which can be considered as a form of multimedia.
